Material Information Summary: Notice of Extraordinary General Meeting – Selective Buy-Back

Key Details:

  1. Selective Buy-Back Resolution
  2. Proposal to approve a selective buy-back of up to 625 million betr Shares (maximum value AUD 200M).
  3. Buy-back price: AUD 0.32 per share (aligned with May 2025 equity raising price).

  4. Conditional on:

    • Successful completion of betr’s all-scrip takeover offer for PointsBet.
    • Shareholder approval at this EGM (special resolution required).

  5. Eligibility & Process

  6. Eligible Sellers: PointsBet shareholders who accept betr’s takeover offer and receive betr Shares, provided they do not vote in favor of this resolution.

  7. Timetable:

    • Record Date for Voting: 23 August 2025.
    • Meeting Date: 25 August 2025.
    • Buy-Back Window: Opens 8 September, closes 22 September 2025.

  8. Funding

  9. Base Case (AUD 80M): Funded from existing cash reserves.

  10. Expanded Case (AUD 200M): Requires:

    • 90%+ ownership of PointsBet (compulsory acquisition).
    • Drawdown under an AUD 120M amended NAB facility (subject to conditions).

  11. Strategic Rationale

  12. Board Recommendation: Unanimously in favor.
    • Optimizes shareholder register by exiting short-term holders.
    • Improves EPS and ROE for remaining shareholders.

  13. Risks: Potential liquidity reduction in betr Shares post-buy-back.

  14. Impact on Capital Structure

  15. Pro forma net cash: AUD 20.1M (AUD 200M buy-back) or AUD 53.9M (AUD 80M buy-back).

  16. Voting power of existing betr shareholders increases post-buy-back (e.g., from 50% to 72% in a 100% uptake scenario).

  17. Additional Notes

  18. No overlap with Offer: Buy-back is separate from the PointsBet acquisition (which proceeds independently).
  19. No director participation: No directors or associates are eligible to sell into the buy-back.

Next Steps: Shareholders to vote on resolution at the EGM on 25 August 2025.

Material Information Summary (ASX Announcement – Southern Cross Gold Consolidated Ltd)

Key Highlights (Exploration Results – Mineralization Expansion)

  • High-grade intersections at Christina prospect (Sunday Creek Project):
  • SDDSC173: 2.9 m @ 16.3 g/t Au (incl. 0.6 m @ 58.0 g/t Au)
  • SDDSC166: 7.1 m @ 4.9 g/t Au (incl. 0.1 m @ 74.8 g/t Au)

  • SDDSC160W2 (record depth): 1.0 m @ 9.5 g/t Au at 926 m depth (580 m below surface).

  • Strike extension to 1.5 km: Mineralized corridor now spans 1.5 km (Apollo East to Christina West), demonstrating lateral growth.

  • Visible gold discovery: SDDSC173 intersected four new vein sets with visible gold, validating geological model.

  • Resource growth potential: Results confirm mineralization extends beyond current exploration targets, with high-grade intervals at depth and along strike.

  • Pending assays: 33 drill holes awaiting results; 8 additional holes in progress.

  • Strategic significance: Antimony-rich mineralization (critical metal) enhances project value amid China’s export restrictions.

Additional Context (Non-Trading Impact)

  • Metallurgy: Preliminary tests show 93–98% gold recovery via conventional processing.
  • Exploration program: Ongoing 60,000 m drilling campaign through 2025.
